---
import SeoLandingLayout from '../../layouts/SeoLandingLayout.astro';
import Card from '../../components/Card.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
import { APP_STORE_URL, isAppStoreUrlKnown } from '../../lib/site';

const appStoreKnown = isAppStoreUrlKnown(APP_STORE_URL);
---

<SeoLandingLayout
	title="Nicotine Pouch Reduction App — Track and Cut Down | Taper"
	description="Taper helps you reduce nicotine pouches gradually with simple daily tracking, progress over time, and a calm, private experience."
	canonicalPath="/nicotine-pouch-reduction-app/"
	h1="Reduce your nicotine pouches in small, manageable steps"
	lede="Quitting cold turkey is stressful. Taper gives you a daily allowance that gradually shrinks, making it easier to cut down on nicotine pouches like Zyn or Velo."
	bottomCtaHeading="Start your gradual reduction today"
	bottomCtaText="Download Taper and set up your daily allowance in less than a minute. No accounts required."
	campaignToken="seo_en_pouches"
	lang="en"
>
	<section class="guide__section">
		<h2>Why gradual reduction works better for pouches</h2>
		<p>
			Pouch habits are deeply tied to our daily routines—driving, working, or after meals. Cutting them all out overnight often leads to an overwhelming relapse because your body and brain expect a constant stream of nicotine.
		</p>
		<p>
			A nicotine pouch reduction app like Taper tackles the problem differently. Instead of asking you to quit today, it drops your daily allowance by one or two pouches a week. Your body barely notices the change, making the withdrawal symptoms far more manageable.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="guide__section">
		<h2>How to use a nicotine pouch reduction app</h2>
		<div class="grid-1">
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>1. Find your baseline</h3>
				<p>Enter how many pouches you use on an average day right now. Be honest. This gives Taper the correct starting point.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>2. Get your daily allowance</h3>
				<p>Taper sets a lock on a daily limit. Try to stay within this number. Having a clear maximum breaks the chain of chain-pouching.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>3. Track with one tap</h3>
				<p>Every time you pop a pouch, log it in the app. Tracking brings awareness to a habit that is usually completely unconscious.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>4. The weekly step-down</h3>
				<p>Every week, Taper reduces your daily allowance by a small percentage. You adapt to the slightly lower nicotine intake over seven days before the next drop.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>5. Coping tools included</h3>
				<p>Used up your allowance but still craving? Use the built-in urge surfing and box-breathing exercises to ride out the craving until it passes.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>6. Private progress tracking</h3>
				<p>Watch your usage slowly trend towards zero. Your data stays entirely on your device because addiction recovery is private.</p>
			</Card>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="guide__section">
		<h2>Common pitfalls when cutting down</h2>
		<div class="grid-2">
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Social triggers</h3>
				<p>Going out for drinks or spending time with friends who use pouches often spikes usage. If you slip up, just track it, forgive yourself, and stick to the allowance tomorrow.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Not tracking every pouch</h3>
				<p>If you take a pouch without logging it, your data is compromised and the tapering math won't work. Log every single pouch, even the extra ones.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Rushing the process</h3>
				<p>Don't try to halve your usage in three days. It defeats the point of gradual reduction. Trust the slow, weeks-long process.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Replacing with other habits</h3>
				<p>Some people start smoking or vaping to compensate. Taper is built specifically to avoid this by making the nicotine reduction so subtle you don't need a heavy crutch.</p>
			</Card>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="guide__section">
		<h2>The ultimate nicotine tracker</h2>
		<p>
			A plan without tracked boundaries crumbles. The subconscious mind loves exceptions. Tracking is central to keeping your promises to yourself.
		</p>
		<p>
			Software like <a href="/">Taper</a> handles the tracking and the math. It turns your daily struggle into lightweight graphics on your phone, without interruptions or accounts.
		</p>
	</section>

	<Section id="faq" title="Frequently Asked Questions" slot="after-guide">
		<div class="grid-2">
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Does Taper work for Zyn and Velo?</h3>
				<p>Absolutely. Taper is designed for any brand or strength of nicotine pouch. Since you log usage by "amount of pouches," the brand does not matter.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>How long does a taper plan last?</h3>
				<p>Most users choose to taper over a period of 7 to 12 weeks, depending on their starting usage and how aggressively they want to reduce.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Is Taper free?</h3>
				<p>Yes. You can download and start tracking your nicotine reduction without hitting a paywall for the core experience.</p>
			</Card>
			<Card as="article">
				<h3>Do I need an account?</h3>
				<p>No. Taper is a local-first app. Your tracking data stays on your iPhone. We don't ask for an email, and there's no cloud sync.</p>
			</Card>
		</div>
	</Section>
</SeoLandingLayout>
